Plot Interaction Effects from a Regression Model

plotint.Rd

This function creates a publication-ready plot of a two-way interaction from various regression models using the emmeans package.

Usage

plotint(
  model,
  effect,
  moderator,
  data,
  mod_scale = "sd",
  type = "link",
  show_ci = TRUE,
  bw = FALSE,
  xlab = NULL,
  ylab = NULL,
  legend_title = NULL,
  pval_position = "none"
)

Arguments

model

A fitted model object (e.g., svycoxph, glm).

effect

Character string. The name of the focal predictor (x-axis).

moderator

Character string. The name of the moderator variable (lines/groups).

data

The original data frame used to fit the model (REQUIRED for survey models).

mod_scale

Method for probing a continuous moderator: "sd" (default) or "quantile".

type

The scale for the y-axis: "link" (default) or "response".

show_ci

Logical. If TRUE (default), plots 95 percent confidence ribbons.

bw

Logical. If TRUE, creates a black and white plot.

xlab

Character string. Optional custom label for the x-axis.

ylab

Character string. Optional custom label for the y-axis.

legend_title

Character string. Optional custom title for the legend.

pval_position

Position for p-value: "bottom.right", "top.left", etc., or "none".

Value

Invisibly returns a list containing 'plot_data' and 'p_value_text'.

  mutate(
    log_cal = log(cal.total),

  model = model_age_cal,
  effect = "age",
  moderator = "log_cal",
  data = mort_data,
  mod_scale = "sd", # Use Mean +/- 1 SD for log_cal
  type = "link",
  show_ci = TRUE,
  bw = FALSE,
  pval_position = "bottom.right",
  xlab = "Age (Years)",

)

  id = ~SDMVPSU,
  strata = ~SDMVSTRA,
  weights = ~WTMEC2YR,
  nest = TRUE,
  data = nhanes_clean
)

# Fit the model: Interaction of Age * BMI on Geometric Mean of BP
# We use gaussian(link="log") to model Geometric Means

  BPSysAve ~ Age * BMI + Gender + Race1,
  design = design_nhanes,
  family = gaussian(link = "log")
)
